# Vendored inside setuptools in the base Python image - not directly exploitable
# jaraco.context path traversal via malicious tar archives
CVE-2026-23949

# wheel 0.45.1 ships in python:3.11-slim-bookworm base image.
# CVE is in `wheel unpack` CLI (path traversal) — never used at runtime.
CVE-2026-24049

# Stored XSS via model description (open-webui < 0.9.0).
# Trivy flags by package.json name+version; the underlying sink in
# Placeholder.svelte / ChatPlaceholder.svelte has been patched in this fork to
# wrap marked.parse() output with DOMPurify.sanitize() — matches upstream remediation.
CVE-2026-44721

# Missing workspace.tools authz check on POST /api/v1/tools/{id}/update
# (open-webui < 0.9.5). Trivy flags by package.json version; the endpoint in
# backend/open_webui/routers/tools.py has been patched in this fork to enforce
# has_permission(user, 'workspace.tools', ...) — matches upstream remediation.
CVE-2026-45395
